KNYSNA - Rescue workers were breathing a sigh of relief on Monday morning as officials declared fires in the greater Knysna area contained.Thousands of people have been displaced by blazes that have been raging for six days.However, no evacuations have taken place since Saturday, when residents of Buffels Kop were moved.They are now being housed at the Hornlee Civic Centre.The death toll in the Garden Route fires has risen to seven and as mop up operations continue, Knysna officials say the town remains open for business. eNCA